  "title": "Financial Advisory Trainee",
  "description": "<p>This is a short, hands-on programme designed for fresh graduates who want real financial skills and exposure to the financial advisory industry. If you're looking for a productive year-end break activity, this program gives you practical money skills and industry mentorship — all in just 3 days.</p><p>What You Will Learn:</p><p> Personal Finance & “Adulting” Skills</p><ul><li><p>Budgeting & saving</p></li><li><p>Insurance basics</p></li><li><p>How to manage your salary after graduation</p></li><li><p>Workplace communication & corporate dressing</p></li></ul><p> Finance & Investment Foundations</p><ul><li><p>Introduction to investing (risk, returns, products in SG)</p></li><li><p>Simple portfolio building</p></li><li><p>Financial planning concepts</p></li></ul><p> Real Industry Exposure</p><ul><li><p>Understand what Financial Advisors do</p></li><li><p>Learn client communication skills</p></li><li><p>Q&A with experienced practitioners</p></li></ul><p>Program Details:</p><ul><li><p>Allowance: $500</p></li><li><p>Duration: 3 days</p></li><li><p>Dates: 25 to 27 March 2026</p></li><li><p>Format: In-person, interactive workshops</p></li><li><p>Location: Paya Lebar Quarters 3</p></li><li><p>Commitment: Full 3 days</p></li></ul>",
